The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, October 21, 2003 				 Mobile firms await big leap
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Oct. 20: Major handset manufacturers are likely to consider setting up production units in the country when the cellular phone market reaches an annual figure of 25-million units. 																								The Indian Cellular Association (ICA) expects the market size to be around Rs 4,050 crore. Of this, mobiles sold through official channels will account for a mere Rs 1,822.50 crore.																								On an average 5 lakh handsets are sold every month through official channels. This year, the handset market is expected to be around 9 million units as against 4.4 million units sold last year. 
